race.comment: SNITZSTREAM (15) has come back in good order this prep with a couple of close minor placings, the latest over 1000m at Eagle Farm where she attacked the line with purpose. Perfectly placed out to this trip at the third run back - she looks ready to break through. BRITANNIA ROSE (11) showed abundant pace when resuming last time out over this distance at the Gold Coast but felt the pinch close to home. Improved at each run of the maiden prep so expect her to make progress today with that first run out of the way. KHOIRGIRL (9) made it four minor placings from five career runs when she found a couple better over this distance at Doomben recently. Needs luck from a tricky gate but she is going too well to leave out. EL CENTRO (7) was lining up for only the second time when she charged home late to grab second over 1100m at the Gold Coast last start. Wide draw the only negative. HANSAGLORY (4) didn't do a bad job on debut last time and will appreciate the extra 200m.
